Creating this detailed infographic within Canva involves combining several design elements and tools available on the platform. 
First, a central background with a blue gradient and subtle digital network lines is applied to set the professional tone. 
Then, a main header text is added using a clean sans-serif font, with key terms like "Digital Literacy" highlighted in a contrasting color for emphasis.

The primary structure is built using four distinct vertical panels, which are created by overlaying colored shape elements with soft, rounded corners and gradient borders. 
This creates a clear visual separation for the different categories.
Inside each panel, the content is organized with smaller text headings and detailed descriptions, utilizing a readable font style.

The illustrative icons are key to the visual appeal; these are selected from Canva’s extensive graphics library and recolored to match the overall palette. Specific logos, such as the Google and LinkedIn marks, are sourced and strategically placed to represent real-world tools.
Finally, small decorative arrows, stars, and dots are dispersed throughout to add a touch of dynamic energy and guide the viewer's eye.
